Sacramento Pikeminnow or Squawfish (Ptychocheilus grandis) can be found in Putah Creek and Cache Creek watersheds. Considered by many as a nongame fish, pikeminnow provide a decent sport on light gear. Found in low to midelevation streams and rivers, pikeminnow feed on insects, small fish, and amphibians. Pikeminnow can reach lengths of up to three feet but are commonly found up to 16 inches.
